A particle is confined in a one-dimensional potential well given by the function: 

V(x) = {0, if 0 < x < a ; ∞, otherwise}

Where 'a' is the width of the well. If the energy of the particle is given by E = 2 eV and the mass of the particle is m = 9.11 x 10^-31 kg, determine the wave function of the particle using Schrödinger's equation.
